OL,3,CPlaid Cymru's challenge has just begun
OL,4,Cas it enters government for first time
OL,6,FThe Institute for Fiscal Studies says
OL,7,FPlaid Cymru's manifesto commitments
OL,8,Fwould require either substantial
OL,9,Fspending cuts or tax rises.
OL,11,FHe is also likely to govern without a
OL,12,Fmajority, meaning compromise and
OL,13,Fnegotiation with political rivals will
OL,14,Fbecome a defining feature of this new
OL,15,Fera in Welsh politics.
OL,17,FFor Plaid Cymru, today is the
OL,18,Fculmination of a project that has
OL,19,Ftaken nearly a century. For Rhun ap
OL,20,FIorwerth, the far harder task begins
OL,21,Fnow.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
